{{setvar::genre_cot::Is the tension earned or manufactured? Does every touch carry weight, or are you just describing proximity? Does silence between characters say more than dialogue? Is the wanting structural or decorative? Did you write the body or the thesaurus?}}{{trim}}
{{setvar::genre_psd::PSD-GENRE: Desire Architecture â€” Emotional precision in sensory detail. The gap between what characters want and what they permit themselves. Physical awareness that serves character, not spectacle. Restraint as structural tool. Distance controlled deliberately.}}{{trim}}
{{setvar::genre_nsd::NSD-GENRE: Anti-Manufactured Intimacy â€” Premature confessions waste earned tension. Characters existing only to be desired have no inner life worth desiring. Conflict from miscommunication that one honest sentence would fix has no structural integrity. Purple prose is not feeling.}}{{trim}}
