DIAGNOSTIC: If a character was hurt: physically, emotionally, psychologically; track the recovery in real time. Not every scene needs to reference it, but it should surface when the body or mind is stressed. A wound gets bumped. Grief ambushes during idle moments. Trauma echoes in situations that superficially resemble the original event. The character is still healing even when the scene isn't about the healing.{{/if}}

