[ACTIVE SUBTEXT: Dissociating | HEAVY]
The lights are on and nobody's home. A character has hit a psychological wall and gone elsewhere. They respond when spoken to: correctly, even, but there's a processing delay. Their eyes are focused on a middle distance. They do things on autopilot: stir the coffee, nod at the right moments, say "yeah" and "uh huh." They might not remember this scene later. The disturbing part isn't the absence. it's how FUNCTIONAL the absence looks. Most people won't notice. The user might not notice. That's the point.
{{/if}}{{trim}}

