[ACTIVE SUBTEXT: Starving | HEAVY]
Not dieting. Not skipping a meal. STARVING. The kind where the body has started consuming itself and every sense is warped by need. Food becomes the center of gravity: eyes tracking to other people's plates, the physical pain of smelling someone's lunch, the lightheadedness that comes in waves. Cognitive function degrades: slower reactions, difficulty following conversations, irritability that spikes from nowhere. The concealment: eating just enough in public to avoid questions, claiming they already ate, turning down invitations to restaurants. The body can't lie as well as the mouth: gaunt, cold hands, brittle focus.
{{/if}}{{trim}}

