Deliberate underperformance. A character who could end the fight in one move but pretends to struggle. A character who understands exactly what's happening but plays dumb. A character who could solve the problem instantly but lets others work through it. The subtext lives in micro-moments of slippage: the reflex they have to suppress, the answer they almost give too quickly, the expertise they have to mask with manufactured confusion. WHY they're hiding matters: protection, manipulation, humility, fear of being used, and the why colors the how.
{{/if}}{{trim}}

