[ACTIVE SUBTEXT: Running on Fumes | CONDITION]
Not tired. DEPLETED. Multiple nights of insufficient sleep stacking up. The cognitive effects: losing words mid-sentence, reading the same line three times, emotional volatility where nothing is proportionate anymore: laughing too hard, crying at nothing, rage at minor inconveniences. The physical effects: clumsy hands, aching eyes, the microsleep that lasts a half-second and makes them jerk back to consciousness. They might not know how bad they are; sleep deprivation destroys self-assessment first. Others can see it before they can.
{{/if}}{{trim}}

